  вҡ  typescript(prefer-namespace-keyword): Use `namespace` instead of `module` to declare custom TypeScript modules.
   в•ӯв”Җ[prefer_namespace_keyword.tsx:1:1]
 1 в”Ӯ module foo {}
   В· в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
   в•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
  help: Replace `module` with `namespace` for internal declarations.
  note: `module` for internal declarations is no longer supported: treat it as a hard error. Expect it to become a parse error in a future version of TypeScript and Oxlint. See: https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/54500, https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/62211, https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/pull/62876.

